tarted in business in - 1939. The war started in - 1938. Or 38/9, well how I went in business - I left the foundry, they had a new foreman come and we didn't agree, well I left the foundry and I was working in the mill on maintenance, well when I was work
i
ng in the mill you see I was registered at the labour exchange as an ironmonger. See? Well they were looking for all iron moulders for munitions. Well I had word from the manager that he was after me for me trade. And he didn't want to lose me, 'cos I was
 on maintenance. And - he said -
