Oh I had a good start. I had a good start. And of course I had to work, the business up. Well then I bought that land down by the station to develop, and as I say the war didn't finish 'til 1946, I went six years from 
1940 to - 1946 - then I submitted plans to develop the business down there, and they wanted that field for the road to go straight through, I couldn't let - develop it. And - after - well I went on then for twelve, eighteen months, and this place had clos
ed, the blacksmith had retired through health, this was closed for two years, and - then eventually I took it. And -
