at did us tell you, we should have won it last year if you'd played, but then I ain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745875\charrsid11994791 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
t having that. I can't agree, because one player - I know - to be honest I like - I love me game of bowls. I love me game of bowls. And - I shall be playing now 'cos I shall
 have the time. Well - we play - we've got two cups we play for. One of 'em I've won twice. One I've won once, I've won the pairs, I've won the handicaps, I've won all the competitions. Well to be honest - last season I didn't enter be - for the simple re
a
son I like in a small club give somebody else a chance. I've got three cups in there I've won. And - now - it is interesting but when I went in Torbay for me operation - I happened to go in the ward, they took me in a ward where the - the - the - chap cal
l
ed Causton - he was the - he - what was he, secretary of the Mid Devon League, and he used to arrange a lot of our matches with touring clubs, Cornwall Country, and Devon Police and all that sort of thing. And he used to contact our secretary, and he said
,
 here - try and get Mr Carne and Denny Mutton to play in a match coming off perhaps in a week or fortnight's time, and believe me, we had two from Brixham and us two, and - never lost a match. Two years ago we went down to Looe, and we played the stronges
t
 rink they had. And - we - at teatime we were fifteen all. We come out after tea, and we beat 'em - twenty-five fifteen, they didn't score. And of course poor old Fred and he - well he was eighty-one in hospital, the poor chap he died, but when he saw me 
c
ome in that ward - he said to me, good heavens, fancy you - what's your trouble? And I told him, he had the same trouble. But unfortunately - he had ulcer or something on his bladder after the operation the poor chap died, just after I come out. But - the
 
bowlers we had to - that come in that hospital to see us, and of course they knew me as well, and half of 'em - spent their time with me and half with Fred. You see? And - well honestly - it killed a lot of time in there. Well - the last match I played la
s
t season - at Teighnouth, we played Cornwall Country Executive. And - us four - when we finished our game, we come in and Fred was - Fred Causton was marking the board, and he said, how did ee get on then? And I said, oh we won. He said, what's your score
?
 I said, thirty-six six. He said, what? I said, thirty-six six, that's what we won by. And he didn't half chuckle. He - he - you can see that's the sort of thing he used to love, and appreciate, and - naturally I was a bit of a idol with him, but - coming
 back to the game, well I - I - I really love me game of bowls.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about this football and cricket, what position did you play at football when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh I used to play inside right. I played for Rangers here for a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you play for a team in Cornwall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, I played for Liskeard. My eldest brother, he was a good footballer, he played for 'em. He played for Looe. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there any books in the house in St Kean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well - you know - 'til a - I'm afraid
 - I can give you some of the history of the village. I can give you some of the history. One thing is St Kean Well, a whishing well. Which is very very popular everybody knows St Kean well - wishing well, and - the - the history of it is that - centuries
 
and centuries ago - before a couple got married - one of 'em would go to the well and get a - bottle of water, and - whoever it was would be master of the house for life. That's sort of thing. You can get the history of - of the village from Cornish peopl
e. I can put ee in touch with people down there who can give you the history of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 But would there be many sort of magazines and newspapers around your own house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, I haven't go anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Not on Cornwall, I mean just in general, did your father keep any books himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well, yes, he used to but of course I'm afraid a lot of it's been - destroyed. There's one thing I have got that he bought, I've got the history of the Great War, the first world - world war, I've got the whole volu
mes of those. But the village itself, of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did he do much reading on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh he did - oh yes, quite a lot of reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of things would he read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well everything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you remember them ever reading aloud to you or to each other, your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well not really, no, because I mean there's - when we got old enough in business his time was occupied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you can remember being a bearer at funerals, can you remember any family funeral in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well yes, now in Cornwall - at funerals - they always used to have - their - nearest friends to a funeral. But up here it's vastly different, the undertaker - arranges all that, but in Cornwall I'll say that, they all select their own bearers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Can you remember any funerals in your own family when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well yes, quite a number. Quite a number but the same thing apply. We always have our close friends as bearers. Never leave it to the - to the - undertaker to to -
 select bearers. Now - confidentially between you and I here, because I've been a bearer at quite a number of funerals and - there's quite a lot of retired men 'cos they're paid these days for it, but in those days when I was home they wouldn't think of b
e
ing paid. But here like - the bearers are paid. Now personally - I think the system in Cornwall is more appropriate. See? I mean - it wouldn't be no trouble, you'd say to your closest friends - would you be a bearer to Uncle's funeral, whoever it was, and
 they wouldn't - never know 'em object yet. Never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 If it was a close funeral in your own family what would happen after the funeral, would you go back to somebody's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh go back to the house and - have a bit of a reunion. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours or friends and relations very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well - what - what do you mean, go out for a social affair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Or just go round for a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well we - we - we did in - in our little way, because you apprecia
te in those days there was no transport, we had to either - walk or - push bike, whatever it may be. Oh yes, we used to have - in fact - my pal when I was home, a chap called - Bill Clapp, we were about the same age, well I used to go down to his place an
d play games evenings and all that sort of thing. And he used to come up with me in - in our own little place and do the same thing and all that sort of thing. That's how we used to carry on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you ever go visiting relatives very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Oh yes, always - always go to - visit our own relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would they come over to see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes. Yes in fact we used to do that a lot more in those days than they do in these days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were your relatives very far away,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh, situated all over the place, most of 'em in Cornwall of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you ever taken shopping, did you ever go shopping with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well no, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you ever go out with just your father on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Where would you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well when he - when I was a little kiddie when he started - when he was in this small way I used to go - we had a - he had a - little pony cart, perhaps he'd deliver something to a farmer and I used to go with him. Yes. I always r
emember one instance - when we was at St Kean, we had to go down the Bodmin Valley, with - something, and - in this little pony cart things, and he always used to carry his gun with him. And I can see him now shooting a rabbit down in the Bodmin Valley. Y
es. And I could show you almost the spot now where he - where he shot that rabbit. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You used to go out quite a lot in the pony and trap with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Go quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you ever go out in the pony and trap as a family to visit relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes. Father used to take us in to Liskeard to see his sister, the - the old maid who used to keep lodgers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you didn't really go out on holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Never had a holiday in me life. Not what you call a holiday. Nev
er. Not in me - days before I was married nor since I've been married. Never could get my wife to leave the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How would you spend Saturdays in those days at ST Kean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, used to go as I say rabbiting in - football and - summertime, cricket and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you a bowler or a batsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, I could bowl. I was a good bowler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say on Sunday you'd go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh always Sundays, very str - father was very strict Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were your parents Methodist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Fathe
r - parents were Methodist. But - you see, the wife's people were church people. And - naturally when I was courting with her I used to attend Duloe church instead of me own home church. That's what I done and - and - the vicar - was - I always remember w
h
en I said well I shall have to give up blowing the organ, and he was really perturbed about it. And I told him why. I said, well my - lady friend lives at Duloe. And I said naturally - we attend - we shall attend Duloe church, that was quite all right. We
l
l then he contacted Barrington Ward you see, and explained the position, well of course Barrington Ward owns everything, and all the chaps who were there, we were - socially attached, because Duloe was a fairly big parish, and they had a gymkhana committe
e for instance, and of course naturally I was one of the committee. See I had an interest then in their village, and I used to go over and - and - and help them and - attend the church and - ring there and everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How often would they have a gymkhana?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well once a year. Once a year. Gymkhana meeting. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they have many point to points and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, they used to have those sort of - functions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about hunting and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, they used to do hunting but - I don't suggest I was interested in hunting. But - lot of the farming community used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about the chapel, were there many social activities organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, just the same as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of things would they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well outings and - little social - evenings, they used to get choirs to come there from other villages, and - 'cos ours was a very - St Kean's a very small village, but they used to get - choirs from - now St Pinnoc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7745875\charrsid11994791 k for instance, where father en}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
ded up, they had a very strong choir there at St - at - the chapels called Colin - Colin chapel, that's where my mother was buried. And - they'd got a really strong choir. In fact my sister attends there now and her husband. Me youngest sister, they l
ive at - \{BLANK\} and me eldest sister, she married a farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they have anything like a Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, Band of Hope meetings. Very strong. Very strong Band of Hope meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your mother go along to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. In fact we 
- they had a little choir, my mother was a good singer, she sang - she sang in the choir, that was when I was quite young. And we were - used to go to Sunday school. Well up to we were say - ten, eleven year old. Because - that's just when I started to go
 to church you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you say that you were in a choir as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No, I wouldn't have been in a choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, he wasn't in a choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did she ever sing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well - just her own little way you know, for herself. For herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you had an organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh we had an organ, yes, and me elder sister, she learnt to play and she could play very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would your mother and her get together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh they used to have a little does together of course. Natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of things would they sing, hymns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745875\charrsid11994791 Oh hymns chief}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 ly. Chiefly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you had more to do with the church after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well you see when I - when - like all youngsters they - they went to church, and - as I say
 I started - blowing the organ because - it is difficult in these little places to get anybody to do it. And - the reason I - took it up was - the - chap that worked at the rectory, 'cos he used to - vicar used to keep a cow or two and this chap worked th
e
re, and I was friendly with his sons, and they got me to come to church, well then they couldn't get nobody to blow the organ, and at - Crabb his name was, organist, he was a farmer, and he used to - that's how it started, he used to come over - once or t
w
ice a week for a little practice, well perhaps of a Wednesday evening for about half an hour, and - couldn't get nobody to blow the organ, and - Crabb worked at the rectory asked me, he said, here would you - 'cos he was relation to Crabb the farmer, he s
a
id, would you go over and blow the organ for Cyril? And I said, oh I don't mind. And that's how I - took it on, well then the vicar said well - would you do it - and - I think they used to pay me about two shilling a month. That's all I used to get, in th
ose days. And of course that was - that was a - that was wonderful. Wonderful job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you go on any sort of church outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - well the ringing festivals. We used to go every Easter Monday, ringing festival.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Where would that be held?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Held - separate place each year. There was quite a number of parishes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would it be competitions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh yes. Yes. South East Cornwall Bell Ringing Association. There was St Kean where I was to, Duloe, Flint, Lanreth - Lanreth - oh I could reckon 
up any amount of 'em, St Neot, and - St Thebe, and - oh I could I think I could reckon up quite a lot. And we all used to meet each Easter Monday. And of course some towers had so many - oh St Martins by Looe, was another, Morvel. See? All these places. W
ell some - some - towers had three - three sets of ringers. At St Kean we had two. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So there was loads of things going on around the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, that was a wonderful day out that was, Easter Mondays. That was the same day that Cornwall Coun
try had their - had their cup finals. See? Because when I got older, not long before I come up here, I used to go to the Cup Finals. But I rang -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was that football now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Beg pardon? Oh yes, Cornwall Country, they - they have their - Cornwall Coun
try Cup Final and the runners up the same day, either at Crewe or St Austell. But - when I was home ringing right up 'til - well I was up in me - just before I come up to Buckfastleigh, I used to go ringing festival.
