\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your father have anything like that? Where he went through the Liberal MP with any problem?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well of course it's rather awkward for me to say because - I assume yes, because he had his problems same as everybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was there much contact between the MP of the area and the constituents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well yes. Oh yes, they used to - automatically come and have meetings, even in the - not only in the towns but in
 the villages to keep contact, that is part of their job. You got to keep contact with the constituents. But where you've got a - a - a - a MP that is in contact, especially with individuals, it makes a vast difference. And whatever your problem is it's t
heir duty to - to do their utmost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you know if your father was ever under any real pressure to vote for a particular party from the farmers for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 He was his own man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. Never took any active part in politics. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 It was only your father in fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That's all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did he work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh he'd definitely, used to speak at meetings. In those days - Isaac Foot
 the solicitor in Plymouth was a very very popular Liberal in Corn - Cornwall, he was a very smart MP.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Is he the father of Michael Foot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That's right. That's right. His father. Michael Foots father. John Foot's father 'Course they boys are cleve
r, you see they had the - they had the education, Fir John Foot's a Labour man. Right Labour man. See there's a - his father a staunch Liberal, and yet his son is Labour. Michael's a Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 I suppose Labour took over from a lot of Liberals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 O
h yes. Liberal - Liberals are nearly a thing of the past. In fact that's - that's one reason that I voted Conservative here, because there's no doubt about it, he - he's - he's a very useful member.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Mr Moreby now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Mr Moreby. He's represented Tot
 - Totnes for many years. We've had one or two very good men put up here, Liberals now, voted for 'em but - it - it's - it's a wasted vote. Definitely.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there any Liberal clubs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Any what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Liberal clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, definitely, Liskeard is - headquarters, Liskeard Liberal Club. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Is that a political thing or just a social thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh social as well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did he used to go along to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, but he - he didn't take a lot of - interest in soc
ial affairs. I was a member of Liskeard Liberal Club for years-. I used to play billiards there. Well in those days I don't know whether I mentioned it - a day or two ago, but - when I was learning me trade father used to give me a shilling a week. And Sa
t
urday evenings I used to go in Liskeard, friend of mine from St Neot where I was born - tuppence, down - he was a member of Conservative club. We went down there and - and had a game of billiards, tuppence, and then come out and went in the fish and chip 
shop and had a feed, good feed for sixpence. Ten pence, and enjoy ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So that would be your big fling of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh we had a - we really used to enjoy ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would that be about the only time you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well that's the only time we could afford to. And that was when I was a teenager learning me trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you remember if your father was a member of anything like a sick club or a savings club of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, I don't think so. Not to my knowledge.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Now how did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh, quite all right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you play with them very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - yes, but - me second brother in Africa, we didn't agree too well, we - we used to have our little splutters. That's when father
 used to - go for us a bit. But - as - he was a - a - a chap that - well, he - he - I was always keen on saving money but brother Jack, he liked to spend it and he liked travel, in fact he went to Africa, he's in Africa now, he's retired now of course. He
's been home three times since he's been there but - he's been out there fifty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did the other two brothers help in the foundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, oh yes. All of us. Yes. All of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So they\rquote d be there before you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Oh yes. Long before me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Now how did you get on with the other brother and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh, quite all right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was there any one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well me eldest brother naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What's happened to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh he's - when we - in 
the early twenties when we had to - move from down there we couldn't live there - he went to - first to Torrington, then he moved to Sal - South Molton, only a matter of about a couple of year after and he's been there ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What's he do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
With one - oh in - agricultural engineering. He was in one firm for about forty-five years, at - South Molton. But he's now retired. Well he - he went about - oh he must - Will have went sixty-five - his - nearly - well he was seventy when he retired
 but he is retired now, 'cos the firm changed hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say the foundry closed, did it close altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, we had to close it altogether.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What did your father do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh he - he - he - worked in the blacksmith's shops for - s
ort of - temporary but eventually he - he went a manager - works in another villages. You see. Well then I carried on and I was the youngest, I - I wasn't very old then, 'cos I left home - before I was twenty, and - I carried on for a couple - struggled o
n
 for a couple of years after, that's when I used to go me post round, and feed me pigs, and - pigs that I - money I made with the pigs I had to help keep me brother, he was rearing up his two daughters, he couldn't earn enough in the business and - I had 
to keep them going until such time we was forced to move. That's why I come to Buckfastleigh. And worked at my trade in the foundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How did you get to know about the job at Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh it's advertised in the Morning News. And through busin
ess connections, the firm knew our firm and - no trouble, I got it quite easily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 I suppose there were so few skilled blacksmiths around in those days anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well - there were rather more then than there is now because as I say - jobs weren't
 easy to get. Oh no, it wasn't easy to get a job in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 But I suppose having a definite skill you'd be better off than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh definitely, and where you had your - more or less brought up in your own business experience you see, I was
 - I was - my father always used to - to push us boys now get on with it, never - never - fast enough, and he used to say - see what Uncle Tom turns out up to Anthony, as if we could - we was - a long way behind him you see, that sort of thing. Used to pu
sh us, well we were taught to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you remember where you lived in St Kean did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Exactly the same. We were all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 There was no real difference between yourselves as blacksmiths and farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
No, farmers - no, all the same, we all - mucked in together. 'Cos we was all in the same position. They were struggling the same as we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 There was no case of skilled craftsmen looking down on others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. None - none whatever. Got on quite well socially.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You hear about people dividing society into different groups in those days,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, well - there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you think of some people belonging to one group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You'd get - y
ou'd get isolated cases but very few. You'd get perhaps - to put it in plain English - a farmer family that was in - good way of doing, they would, shall I say, snub the likes of others you see that were struggling. But - generally speaking they got on ve
ry well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So there was no sort of real splitting apart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh no. No. No, because - some of my friends that are - are now my age - that were in a very good way of doing, we used to play cricket together, football together, billiards together, ringing
 together, and - no - no trouble, socially got on wonderfully well. Wonderfully well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about the vicars and people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - fine, no trouble. Got on - really tip-top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Who were considered the most important people in St Kean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Nobody. Nobody in particular, we were all on the same footing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You'd come into contact with people like the vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, yes, and - you do in small rural areas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there any doctors around at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, the doctors - ou
r doctors from Liskeard of course. There was no - doctors in the villages, they all have to come from the towns. And in those of days of course - in our early days they used to ride horseback. No such things as cars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Where would they lived, they lived inside the town itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
They live in the town, most of 'em - adjoining their surgeries. Our doctor and - he was called Nettle, Doctor Nettle, very old fashioned family doctor, wonderful doctor. Wonderful doctor he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say your mother was quite often sick, what would happen when she was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh we had neighbours, neighbours would help.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you have any relatives coming round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes, all the same, relatives and neighbours. Well of course were were fortunate you see, 
we had me eldest sister was a mainstay - at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 She stayed at home did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
She was at home yes. She - she was home - oh - sister must have been - in her 30's when she married, rather more because in those days they hadn't got the money to set
tle down. And her husband was home with his father you see. When she married she went to live with them. On the farm. They couldn't go off on their own farming. He worked home. Practically - practically all his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You said you had a younger sister didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 I had a young sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you remember what happened when she was born, how old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well I was - what's - what's there between me and Dorothy? About fourteen, fifteen years difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 The youngest one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, that's the youngest one. Youngest sister. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Can you remember what happened when she was born, did you have a midwife in or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well no, no, just a - the neighbours would help, 'cos in those days - in those days all t
he mothers had their children at home. Vastly different now, they're - they are watched and they get the - treatment automatically, but in those days - in fact my wife when our daughter was born since I've been to Buckfastleigh, that was in 1926 - we were
 
- oh no, wait a minute, in 1929, I come here in 1925, we come in - 1930 me daughter was born, little over twelve months after we married we had our daughters, is only one we've got and the same thing applied in those days in 1930 - they had their - babies
 
at home. But incidentally the doctor that brought my daughter into the world, she's just passed away yesterday. Doctor Ironsides. Yes. Well she's gone. It's in the morning news. At three thirty in the night - and - I - walked over in the gardens, naturall
y
 I could hear the wife up - moaning and groaning a bit, and - when she had her pains and - when I come back, I heard the baby crying. So naturally - I went upstairs and doctor heard me coming, she said, oh you can come in. And she said, there you are, you
've got a nice little daughter. And she everything's all right and I shall be coming to see you in twelve months time. But - we never had any more. No. But - the carry on in those days were much the same as they were in the earlier days, when I was born.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No relative would come to stay the night or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh they would if they were wanted of course, but as I say we were fortunate - to have good neighbours and - and the elder sister home. There was no such thing as going to hospital for maternity cases in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well yes, when - especially when she had these epileptic fits. You used to get people come in and help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That would be mainly neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, all neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of things would they do to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh washing and cooking and - anything general cleaning, making the beds and - so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you say your parents had many relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well Liskeard, they were in Lis - Liskeard area. They were all in the Liskeard area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How much would you really see of them, would you see them very regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Frequently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you go to Liskeard and they come to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, we'd go Liskeard and they'd come to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You were saying about Christmas Eve dinner down at your aunt's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Yes, well - periodically they used to - pop in and - and of course there wasn't no such thing as telephones in those days, they used to just come and go. No such thing as telephones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 There were no such things as invitations and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. None whatever. Popped in any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 The same applied to friends and neighbours did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Exactly the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you remember if there was any particular time when friends would pop round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
No, just - any time. When they - felt that probably you was in need of anything or - just pop in and say, well, is everything all right? And, well I'll see ee again later and - somebody or other practically every day you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your father and mother have many friends around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh my word, yes, plenty of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would they go out and see them very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, when - well they could of course. Yes, whenever they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Exactly the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When you were still at school do you remember whether - where you would play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh we had our playground and we had a playing field. Yes, we used to play - in the yard - various games and of course do
wn in the field - cricket and football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about in St Kean, where would you play there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well there we used to play in the farm field, we - farmers - there was plenty that would - let us have - in fact - just opposite my shop we had a nice playing - field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So there was plenty of open space to muck around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Plenty of open space.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of thing did you usually play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Beg pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of things would you play, football and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh football and cricket of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you allowed to get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh my word, well that - naturally.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have any hobbies apart from gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well - not - they used to - that would be hobbies. The gardening and of course - winter time chi
efly, evenings, the billiards. Billiards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you keep any pets and things like that those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Used to keep cats and dogs. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 It sounds a veritable household of animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well that's always the case in the country with
 families. You see now here - it's hopeless to keep an animal, or a - anything, cats or dogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you collect anything in the time when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Like stamps or butterflies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh I used to - collect cigarette cards. Used to be very fond of - cigarette cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of things were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - players used to - issue - cards or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You were saying about these Player's cigarette cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, well you see they issue - they - used to issu
e series. Sometimes fifty or a hundred - of each - product, railway engines, race horses, football - players, of all football teams, all that sort of thing, historic buildings and - you see, used to be series of them. In some cases fifty, in some cases or
 a hundred whatever it might be and I used to save quite a lot, but of course - what happened to them - goodness only knows, over the years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Nowadays you collect them and you get prizes and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, stamps now you see. Stamps. Green Shield stamps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you ever have anything like stamps in those days, collecting stamps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes - there was - in some cases - yes, in some cases.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 But you didn't actually collect stamps yourself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. Just couldn't be bothered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you ever go fishing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Well yes, I did do a bit of fishing. My school-friend, he was - just my age, reared up with him and poor chap he's dead and gone, only about twelve months ago, and - his father was a rabbit trapper, and as I've said be
fore, he used to go fishing more or less for the family fish, feed, that was the object, but he was fond of fishing and of course this boy took on fishing and I was going to school and I always remember what happened. Arthur always on to me about fishing,
 
and - I made a rod of me own, and I went in the woods and cut a lot of stick, you - in the woods they grow thin - and - I had a rod and line and I remember the first time I went in fishing, that old river from Liskeard to Looe, it's a - if you get - heavy
 
showers of rain in the fishing season the water would be muddy and fish would bite much better then than they would in clear water, 'cos in clear water they usually fish with fly. Well, I went - down with Arthur this particular day and I caught three beau
t
iful trout and - of course I haven't got the patience to stay in one pool very long if I didn't get a bit in about five minutes I was gone on to the next pool. And - Arthur's father who was fishing down there same time and Arthur was fishing, and I overto
o
k his father and he said, have you had any luck? I said, yes, well I was really proud of these fish, and he - he said my word - wonderful job. Well then I went down again a time or two after and didn't get a bite, that finished it. That finished it. But I
 
always remember on instance when father was in business, we used to get a farmer - we used to get a traveller for a firm, very fond of fishing and he used to come to Cornwall, and I used to take him up the Drains river, that's the - the Drains River, up -
 Bolventa come down that valley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was that near Liskeard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
It's near Bodmin, up close where I was born, and - father used to say when I was a boy, he'd say, well - you know your way up Drains River, you go up with Mr - Thomas his name was, always r
emember his name, and we went up, I used to go up with him fishing and he, my word, he could fish. I've seen him catch as many as thirty or forty trout - in a day. And he used to love it. He used to love it, you - 'cos you see in those - in the West Count
r
y you wouldn't get so many fishermen as you get up further up, and that's why he used to come down there, and he used to really enjoy his fishing. And of course I knew the - the farmers - through father, up that valley and - somebody would spot us, and th
ey'd say, oh come up - our place and have a cup of tea. They was really - and of course they used to - as I've - told you, they used to - be self-supporting, make up their own bread in these - open chimneys. In their bread pans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So you used to go up to the farmers quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You took part in football and cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there things like cinemas in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, Liskeard. Liskeard was the - in fact the owner of Liskeard cinema - took 
over Buckfastleigh cinema - just the same time I come here. That's how we were so pally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of films would they have on down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, all types of films of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How many times a week would they run them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh every night in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you very often go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
At home occasionally. When I could afford it. But when I come to Buckfastleigh I used to go fairly regularly for the simple reason that - friends I used to work with here - used to go and of course Pickles
 I knew so well that - well it was the only thing that I had to do for leisure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How much did it cost to go in Liskeard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh it was only a copper or two in those days, tuppence or three pence. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your parents ever give you pocket money when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, yes, but very little if we get - if we get a copper or two a week it would be - as much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of thing would you spend the money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh sweets of course. I mean my word for a penny then you could get enough sweets to last you a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you free to play with anybody you liked in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 There were any children your parents would discourage you from playing with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, none whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When friends came round to the house would they be offered things to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Well they more or less - more or less - did the same thing as they would if they were home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you say that the friends who came round were your mother's friends or would they be your father's friends or friends of both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no, the same, everybody was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
People say that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with friends or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well, of course - there wasn't a very much time for actual amusements. You see, there was always something to do, something wanted to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So it was mainly sort of talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. That - that's right, yes. Father was - he - he was very kee
n on cricket or footballer any - clean sport, but as I say - gambling no. Racing he was dead against. All that sort of thing. Cards, where there was gambling attached. But football or cricket or any social affairs - quite different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 He took part in that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say that in those days there weren't really any distinctions between the different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So everybody mixed up with everybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there any sort of gentry tupe people about that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Well of course you used to get exceptions as I say. But - very few. Just get the odd exceptions. I remember one instance, a farmer's son, they were - more or less you could say gentry class of people, and - the son 
- I was attached to, this was at Duloe where my wife come from, and he was on the gymkhana committee, well naturally we were pals together, and I remember when his father in those days, when they were self-supporting, they - when the time come you could b
u
y oil engines and farm machines to - prepare their own - corn for their cattle, 'cos previous to that they always had to go to the mill for everything, take their corn - grain to - to the mill to be prepared, but the time come when they put in their own e
q
uipment. And in this particular case, Brown his name was, I always remember it, he - decided to put in an engine, and - he was going to a firm called Glenn and Morcambe at Liskeard, you see, and his son said, well - you got to get this engine from Mr Carn
e
, and - Brown was a staunch Conservative and of course father was a Liberal that they didn't used to get on very well, but eventually the son got his way, and - naturally through our attachment - and - we supplied the equipment for him. But if it hadn't b
een for our - connections, the - son's - father wouldn't have got that business you see. We used to get isolated cases of that description.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 But they were isolated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Isolated -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was it the Churston's you said owned all the land round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Here? In this area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Who owned all the land round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Down there? Yes. A man called Comden - owned - a fair bit of St Kean parish, he - he was a tea-planter in Ceylon. I think it was Ceylon. And - he made a fortune and come home, and - put u
p a - in those days they used to call it a mansion, and - I used to - go down there quite a bit, because the chap that worked for him, a gardener - and his sister worked in the house, and - I used to go there with the post you see, so I used to - intimate
l
y know him very well. And - he was well known then as the squire of the parish. The squire of the parish. In fact the land that I - that I had - used to feed me pigs, belonged to him. And my uncle that was a postman, called Pengelly, when he retired - of 
c
ourse he didn't want the field, and my father - asked squire if he could - have the - field, but - he wouldn't let him have it, but he let me have it. And I was only a boy then. That was when I used to go me post round. He'd let it to me, but he wouldn't 
let it to father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Why was that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Well, because of - he just - he just - appreciated I suppose that - and - and the same thing, politics. That's all it is. And another thing was - his own - sister - farmed the farm adjoining this field
, and they had two sons and we were pally, cricket and football, and the league social affairs, you see, and of course naturally when Squire Condon - said I could rent the field which I did and that's how I had me pick. You see, I took over from me uncle,
 and - everybody was happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was the house rented where you lived?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. As I told you A man called Dawe - Glasgow owned that property.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 But he wouldn't come down very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 About - about once in twelve months used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would he do the repairs and improvements and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, well - yes, he used to do most of the repairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was he a good landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh very good indeed. Yes, very good indeed, very considerate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh chiefly of course the farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about the chapel, who would go to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well ordinary working people. Because in those days there - there was really a distinction between church and chapel. Because my fathe
r was really upset when I went to church. But - he wouldn't narrow - so narrow minded that he - he wouldn't agree, 'cos his and the vicar had - quite a chat about it, and of course - it's quite all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say that everyone was the same, do you remember any family at all that was considered rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well no, not really in those days. Socially they were far different from what they are today, you - there was no such thing as we hearing anybody stealing anything or - or any - any - domestic troubles. Never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You don't remember any drunkenness and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
No. Well they couldn't, they hadn't got the money. The - the - the older generation, yes, you'd get exceptions in the older men, some of 'em - would - would drink, but - gen
erally speaking, especially the younger generation - you'd never hear of any trouble at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was it very easy to move from one group to another in those days, to move up the social ladder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, no trouble at all. No trouble at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about the other way, do you ever remember any cases of people dropping down?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Not to my knowledge. You see, most of 'em in those days - were - well - boiled down to - the - call it higher class if you like and the working class. But you'd get very little of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there many gipsies and travelling people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well had a few gipsies about of course but - the same thing applies there, they were sociable with everybody. And - no trouble at all, generally speaking. No trouble at all. 'Co
s in those days gipsies used to come around with their packs, selling drapery and all sorts of things and - clothes pegs and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Everyone used to like to see them come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Now you hear all this about people hating gipsies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Yes. That's quite - right, but it wasn't so in those days. 'Cos - especially in the country - the people used to look for 'em to come around with their clothes pegs. 'Cos all their clothes were hung up, it isn't like spin driers today
. And - we used to get the French onion men come around. Quite frequently, with onions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Where would they come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well of course - they - they were Frenchmen, they - onions used to come across here and they used to - go around with pushbikes, 
strands of 'em on their pushbike. And they always used to say - shilling a bunch, shilling a bunch, and a penny for myself. Yes. Frenchmen, I can remember it quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were they actual Frenchmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, actual Frenchmen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 They came over from France did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Yes. And they'd - come around to the houses and - naturally nearly all - country people were fond of French onions. And they'd have 'em - strands of 'em on their - bikes and - they'd say, here you are, a shilling. They'd start off p
erhaps - one and three and they'd come down, in the end you'd buy 'em for a shilling or ten pence or nine pence and - and then they'd say, oh and a penny for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you ever have anything like travelling theatres come round, travelling players?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. Don't remember anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Can you remember whether anyone was described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well, no, not in - not generally speaking, you'd - you'd get the odd one or two gentry people of course who were pro
minent in - managing affairs, but - the - in those days - everything was arranged more or less - locally, there wasn't the res - wasn't the restrictions that we've got today. No restrictions in those days like we've got now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you brought up to call anybody sort of master or sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well of course in - the - just the gentry. Now that Squire Condon as - as I knew him. Well - he was very strict with his staff and he had only a matter of about three on that estate, and of course they wer
e very poorly paid. I remember one instance Squire Condon when he died. Clapp this chap was called, William Clapp and we were boys together of course and - he was one of my pals, and - sometime before he died - he'd picked up a - golden sovereign in his y
a
rd. And - oh the boy - William - the gardener picked up this sovereign and 'course naturally he gave it to the squire. He said, I picked up this in the yard. Well the squire put it in his personal drawer I suppose, and he - he had his diary and he made an
 
entry, William Clapp - handed in the sovereign such a date you see, he found in the courtyard, he had - horses and carriages, and - his nephew, one of the executors that settled up all the affairs, went through his diary after the old gent was gone and he
 
come across this. And the sovereign, and he went out in the garden to William, and he said - William, do you remember - finding a golden sovereign in the courtyard? Round about particular time? Oh, he said, yes. He said, what did you go with it? Oh, he sa
i
d, I gave it to master. And - he said, well there you are, that's yours. And he said, why the hell he didn't give it to you - when you - you found it, he said, I don't know, he said, days are different. Days are different. Now when the old chap was - buri
e
d, 'cos I was a ringer as you know, and William was a ringer, but we've often talked about it 'cos a sovereign was a fortune, and we each - each ringer had a golden sovereign for it when he - I've got mine now. Yes. And of course William had one, and the 
one he had give to him, he had two sovereigns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you ever told to touch your cap and things like that to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, definitely, oh yes. I had to use my manners those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh everybody - everybody much the same. Everybody much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well yes, they all did. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh yes, just the same although - father - could be outspoken with - especially in politics, that the only thing. But socially he was very good and - and - and - as I said, the majority used to - appreciate him. J
ust the odd instance where - you get - somebody would be really annoyed with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to any particular group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Can you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well yes, we had our - had our local village policeman. In fact at St Kean there wasn't any but a duty one, he used to cover St Kean, but - nothing, the same as the rest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You were never sort of brought up to worry about policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No
. Now - one thing we in the village used to do, especially summer evenings - and it happened to be - we used to meet outside the church and we used to play what we called duck stone. You've never heard of such thing? Well we used to have a big stone in th
e
 middle of the road, and we'd all have - stones that we could handle, and - stand back so far and throw 'em off and whoever got nearest the big stone was the winner you see. Well - if we - if we saw a policeman coming, we could see - up the village, and -
 we should run up and pick up our stones and hide away. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What would he do if he caught you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well he just - just - warn us - all he'd say, well now be careful of traffic you see. But in those days there wasn't any traffic. You see? You could hear a horse and cart coming, or you could hear anybody horseback. No such thing as cars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was there much scrumpting going on in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well yes, of course you used to get - used to get that sort of thing naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What did the policeman think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Well of course they'd - they'd - they'd just up - warn ee, now say it's wrong, you see, and - I was always taught, father always used to say now, if you want anything ask for it. You see? Well in my particular case I was so 
- attached to farmers and I used to help 'em with the harvest that - they used to say now if you want any apples help yourself, if you want anything help yourself. And in the early twenties - twenties when things were pretty grim - there's one farmer in p
a
rticular used to kill - kill pigs, sheep and even bullocks, and you'd get your share of - meat. Yes. You'd get your share, that was in the days when the sheep for instance - all they could get was a pound for it in market. And farmer Slade used to kill 'e
m, and his - chaps like my - myself would help him, he'd - give you a - a - a piece of lamb or sheep or the pigs the same, pork, mutton, anything. That's how we used to live.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So you don't remember ever being told when you were naughty that your mother would say I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh yes, she - used to say that just to - frighten ee sort of style. And of course we used to take notice of it. They wouldn't take any notice of it today. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You think the police got on OK with the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Smashing. Used to muck in - muck in with us and - football, cricket and - social affairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were they local people, the policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - usually, yes. In fact the policemen that - that I knew so well - was in that one particular village prac
tically all his career. You see? And he was - when there was, well say likely to be a rough house they'd always send for p.c. Bennett. He was - he cold handle anybody. Yes. I've told - I've heard him - he - he come up with me - after I got married, come u
p
 here - he lost his youngest daughter, and I went home for a weekend and met him, and I said - well why don't you bring your wife up sometime for a change? Which - in time he did. He did. And it was - we used to have some really good times together. Reall
y
 good times together. And - oh he's a nice chap. Well he was a chap as I say he was in that village and - and the reason was he got so attached to the place, 'cos - these policemen as a rule after four, five or six years they've got to move, but - Bennie 
always stayed at Duloe. All his career. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you brought up to treat your elders with respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well yes, we had to. Oh my word, they don't take no notice of their parents today. That's why we get so much trouble and crime. Parents aren't 
strict enough with them. Well, you can understand why, because they've got so much money now themselves that - their - their youngsters - they've got the freedom to do what they like and - there's no training or discipline with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What did you think about that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well of course - in my particular case as I got a bit older it was a case of I had to help them. I had to help them. I mean it is a th
ing that - it's a - more or less a private family affair, but I should never regret - regret what I did for my parents. Never. When me wife passed away I - bore all the expense. And the same thing - with father. And during me lifetime all I helped 'em all
 I possibly could, and me brothers and sisters. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What difference would it make to the family when your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well of course - we - definitely stuck together and looked after him but - fortunately he didn't have a lot of illness '
til his last days. And he was eighty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That was only about ten years ago?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did he ever get help from the guardians or the parish or any other charity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Any help with what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 From the guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, my father was too independent. He was too independent for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was there anybody in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no. Nobody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 There was no sort of rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you ever given any lessons by your parents or a tutor or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no, we used to - rely on our schoolteacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh I started school when I was about - four. Yes. Had to in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say it was three miles to Liskeard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Used to walk three miles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you go on your own or would your brothers and sisters be at that school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh there was one or two others used to walk as well from the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What time of the morning did you go when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Well you'd leave eight o'clock and - it was three miles to walk and nine o'clock we start school. Now - always leave an hour, regular as clockwork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You wouldn't come home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No. I bought pasty as I said and - or sandwiches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What were school hours, nine o'clock 'til when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Come out at four o'clock, afternoons. Used to be home be five, teatime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So that's from four on your did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 'Til you were about eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So you did just sort of do morning school to begin with, then afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Personally, no I hadn't got any interest. But - 'cos I had a - a chat with my schoolmaster after I got in business, and - I - and he - an
d he agreed with me. That She - her husband - was - in to Plymouth hospital to finish his days, he had - well I suppose it was - this arthritis sort of crippled right up with it for years, bed lying for many years, he finished his time in - Broomborough h
o
spital. Well his wife carried on, she used to keep the - little - little village shop here and the sub-post office for along long time, and she had a daughter, married - yes, she had a daughter just up the road here, well when Mrs Southam's husband was in
 
Broomborough we used to go in and see 'em, I used to take her in, and - we saw the last of Mrs Southam. You see? Well this lady that's in with us now was in there, her - her daily help. Well - my wife as I told you haven't enjoyed too good health for a lo
n
g time, well when Mrs Southcombe passed out several years ago - her daughter Betty appreciated what we did for her, and hers hardly a day missed but she comes down, with mother of a afternoon, just to have a cup of tea perhaps sometimes ten minutes, somet
i
mes an hour, well Mrs Watts that was the day - the help in there, the day Mrs Southcombe was buried my daughter said - to mother, she said - now's your chance to get Mrs Watts. So mother said, oh I can manage my work. Her said, now look, I'm going up and 
s
ee Mrs Watts. And she went up and she said - what about coming down a morning or two a week to help do a bit of cleaning for mother? She said - cor, she said, I should be delighted. Only too happy. And she's done it ever since. And she'd a person you can 
t
rust, every Wednesday now the wife and daughter have a day out, she comes down Wednesday morning to do the cleaning. The house is empty. She does the all the cleaning, and - she isn't really paid. She won't accept no more than a few shillings a week, wher
e
as we should normally have to pay probably three times as much, but now for instance - we've got at least - fifteen hundred - weight of coal in our coalhouse - that we've had for three or four years, but we've got everything electricity, well we've - I've
 
give her - I've giver her - I told her I said, you get Fred to come down, he can take away all that coal. You see, that's how we carry on. And they - well they appreciate these things. I got a wood house there with stacks of wood in, now I said, tell Fred
 to clear out that wood, take it home, do him more good than anybody else see, well they appreciate these things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So it's not really died out in the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No, we - we still carry on the same way. She's in there now cleaning today. I belie
ve she comes down - Wednesdays and Fridays I think it is. And then she often pops down just for a cup of tea of a evening or - you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You were saying about the schoolmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Jago his name was. When I used to school - go to school I use
d to go in the blacksmith's shop and blow the fire before I went to school, been to school many time with me hands black as ink, and - practically every morning doctor - the schoolmaster, Jago, he would say - let me see you hands? And he'd say, go and was
h 'em. Used to go in the wash house, go in the wash house, wash me hands. And he used to say to me, you'll never make a man your brother will. Me eldest brother was a good scholar. No doubt about that, a wonderful scholar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Is this the one who went to South Molton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Went to South Molton. Wonderful scholar. He used to say to me you'll never make a man your brother will. Well - I left school at eleven years of age, and of course as I say - worked home until I come to Buckfastleigh, then I was in the f
oundry and when I went -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
What kind of things did you do at school, you were telling me about the schoolmaster saying you wouldn't be as good as your brother, but you learnt enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well - practically - all the lessons are subjects - I seemed 
to have more interest in me home - life. You see? I wasn't a bit interested, in fact when I was eleven year old and I was told that - I could go home to work, 'cos naturally father asked the - education people and there wasn't no such restrictions these d
a
ys as there is now, and - the war was on, and - oh yes, that's quite all right and of course I left, that finished me with school. And as I say, when things appealed to me - I grasp it straight away. Like these percentages, I had it in two seconds. I knew
 
- I had commonsense to know what five percent was. Quite simple. When you sum it up isn't it? Two and a half's half of five, ten is double of five, twenty is - double of ten, see, 'tis simple. Well I - I had no trouble - with percentages after. No trouble
 at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How did you get on with Mr Jago, was he a good teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh he was a first class teacher. And - as I say, my aunt, she used to - she had three schoolteachers, and one of 'em - lodged with her that naturally - if I wanted any help then he would - Pierce his name was, Billy Pierce, and Billy would - help me.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was he a local or would he come from somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh come from Cornwall, he - I think he - Camborne was his native home. He teached at Liskeard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about when you moved to the other school, how old were you when you moved to the other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh when we - well I wasn't there more than about - what would I be, about nine - about nine year old I suppose when me daughter - when me sister, youngest sister - went to
 Trewrdlen school, that was another little village school, then of course - eleven I had to finish, go to - war was on, I had to go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you find much difference between the two schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well yes, you see Liskeard school was very much bigger, more classes. In Trewrdlen school - you were more or less all in one room.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 The young ones and the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, all in one room, in different classes. But Liskeard school each class was in a separate room. Bar the - the senior room w
as a bigger room, they were - there was somewhere about three classes in that room, but the - younger generation were in separate rooms. There was one - for the youngsters, the first classroom, then there was a second classroom I think there was two in th
at class, class two and three, and then you come up in the seniors, in the big room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of things was he keen on, was he keen on things like punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, yes, of course. Always very - strict on that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about manners and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, you had to be. You had to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did he place much emphasis on talking properly and not swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - oh yes, 'cos - teachers - you had to speak English. 'Course - I mean in any district or country you'd got your con
ditions, in Cornwall - they got a distinct - accent from other - counties. You - I mean you take a Cornishman and a Scotchman or a Welshman, they're - their language is - speech is vastly different, and - I was always a typical Cornishman as far as that g
oes, when I come up here see down there we - it is we everything. You see up here it is us. Down there it is we. We did that, we do that, but up here is us did that, us do that. Well that's - that's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What would happen if you did anything the teachers disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well we'd just get the stick, that's all about that. Get the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 They did use the stick then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh they used to use a cane in those days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were they very strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, they were - Jago was very strict. Yes. But - of course now - it is a crime to touch a child with a stick, the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did the girls get the same punishment as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well I wouldn't like to say because the girls were - independent. They - they didn't it wasn't a mixed school. It
 was at Trewrdlen, it was at Trewrdlen but not at Liskeard. All boys school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was it a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh board school in those days. Board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, yes, up to a point of cou
rse in fact - I went to - a private school Saturdays for some time when - when - I was learning to - take an active part in the business. Such as - and that was in the spare time, the books you see. Yes, I think it was Hughes Academy - I think it was Hugh
es Academy, Plymouth, they used to come Liskeard. I used to go there Saturday mornings - when I got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 This was after you left school was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Oh yes. I used to go - Saturday mornings for - lessons, on book keeping mainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 It wasn't a sort of a trade college for learning skills or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you ever go to Tech. College after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have apprenticeships in those days, would you be apprenticed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, there was apprentic
eships for trades. But of course where you'm in hour own business - you can get - you see, I was quite capable of - of - of - of taking a job - when I was fifteen. Now it is a crime to start work 'til they'm fifteen or sixteen. But in those days - if you 
w
ere capable of doing a job, well you could - you could get it. No such thing as unions in those days. No, my word, no such thing in - as union. I'm afraid - I'm afraid - personally, I'm going to speak me mind, unions are ruination of this country. That's 
my candid opinion, whether you agree or not I can't help, that's my opinion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 There wasn't anything like this before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 I quite appreciate that - that - people had hard does in my time, but now it's gone to the extreme. They don'
t care two hoots where they money come from - comes from, and any business, unless you earn enough - to pay all these things, how long can it go on, it's bound to disrupt industry. And if they tell me that nationalisation's going to cure the problem, God 
h
elp us. We've seen that already with the coal mines, the railways. I've got packing cases in that shop now I can't send back because they cost more than the cases were worth. It's coming to something isn't it. And now the railwaymen are still - it wouldn'
t
 be so bad if they did their job. But believe me in latter years - my goods from Paddington, passenger train, at least seven days from Paddington to Newton Abbot. I ask you if there's any reason in that. It - it's - it's facts, and they can't get away fro
m it. It's facts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 I suppose one of the reason is that people are not so interested in their jobs as they used to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, they don't care two hoots so long as they get the money and it is the unions that's causing it. Now in this coal strike, I'm 
open to gamble that at least fifty percent of the men didn't want to come out. Probably a bigger percentage. My councillor's coming for a minute now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your parents ask you what you did at school in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh not - seldom they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they ever visit the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh yes. Now one instance I - I remember quite well. Liskeard market days, my father - used to attend Liskeard markets with these implements, and he knew wh
at time we were - out in the playing field afternoon, and many many times he used to walk up to - 'cos - it's out - or attached to the market, there was a lot of trees, and he used to walk up - and stand on the bank and watch us - children playing. Becaus
e - and see, and - of course if - if I catch his eye naturally - yes, good as to say well - you'm happy, many times he did that. So it shows he had an interest in - our school affair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would he pick you up from school at those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no, always used to walk home because - well he used to push bike you see, no such thing as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How would he get his implements into town though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well he - we had a - little pony - cart thing. Little pony trap thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did all the children come from similar types of home to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, most of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no. No such things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No. Everybody - mucked in together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you went on to this school at Trewrdlen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Trewrdlen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That was pretty well the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Just the same. Just the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You don't think you'd like to have stayed on longer if you'd have had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, because when I got to that a
ge as I say when I left school eleven year old, me mind and interest was in the business. I - I was - I was happy as boy blowing the bellows and - and - and making things with the forge, and then of course eventually father said, well - after the - just a
f
ter the war, he said, well now look - you boys learn whatever trade you want. You see, well I was very keen on - iron moulding, and I went in the foundry. And the reason partly was because I was interested in it, and the only man we had there was - he was
 - retiring age, and I took over from him and - ran the foundry when I was about fifteen. And carried on up to the - twenties. 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 There was the foundry, was there any other parts of the business as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, the fitting shop and - fitting shops and the blacksmiths shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So you were mainly to do with the foundry or did you help in all of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh I did a bit in each - what we used to do, I used to go in the foundry perhaps for about - two or three weeks, and then we'd cast - som
ewhere about two tons of castings well that would last us for perhaps two months. Then I'd go out in the blacksmiths shop and help - forging and assembling implements, and painting, I used to do the painting. You see? But you see with industry today - eac
h man got his job. And as I say there wasn't no such thing as unions in our business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you say it was a big concern, it sounds like quite a big place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well - you see in those days - we worked much longer hours. Well from daylight 'til dark, 
and - and it's amazing - the amount of implements we used to produce, besides all the other type work, such as banding wheels, shoeing horses and - laying plough coulters and all that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Plough what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Plough coulters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What are those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 We
ll - flat stem - a flat - tread that used to cut the land, you see, but now it's discs - discs, steel discs. There's none of that now, it's all died out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say when you first started work all these people went off to the first world war? Now how man
y would that leave in the actual foundry and the shop altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, old Tom - all told - when father finished what - what were we - about - somewhere about - five or six people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were three of those your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Two brothers and meself, three - three boys. And - three or four employees. That's - staff we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When you were at school did you have any part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No, no, no, home in our own business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 But did you help in the foundry and the blacksmith shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Wasn't time you see. Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You just used to help out rather than sort of earn money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you had to work from about seven o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well from daylight 'til dark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have Sundays off altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh Sundays, father was very strict with Sunday. He wouldn't - wouldn't allow anything done Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 And you had a half day off Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Saturdays. And as I say I used to - go rabbiting or - summertime cricket of course. Wintertime football. But occasionally go rabbiting.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you got a shilling a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 And seven and six a week for the post round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no, because - as I said - five shillings o
ut to the seven and six post money - I used to buy barley meal. For - barley meal and sometimes - I'd save the other half a crown - and perhaps some weeks I'd have two hundredweight, just depends what pigs I had feeding. And it just depends what - what - 
h
ow the farmers kept me going, 'cos I used to - rely on them for quite a bit. And - I never used to have to say well - Bill, Mr Slade, Bill he was called, I used - never used to say - Bill, I could do with a hundredweight of barley or anything, he - he kne
w
 how I used to run and he'd come in and - say - now - how's your - barrels looking up? That's what he used to say. And - I said, oh I'm getting all right. There's a couple of bags for see. See? He knew exactly how I was running. And I knew exactly how he 
- and - when he wanted me to help with his harvest and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How did younger on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh quite all right. Quite all right. Top hole. Used to help one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You obviously liked the work at the foundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Beg pardon? Oh well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you have any regrets about school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 None whatever, no, I've got no regrets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well - definitely. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How did you get on working with your father, did he treat you like a son or like another employee or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well, he was - he was very strict and I mean he - there wouldn't be no such thing as idling if - you see - stuck about, come on get on with that. Then he'd say sometimes - there yo
u are, there's a set of harrows. You sharpen they tarns and you can leave work. And you used to go like blazes. Well it was good for you if I could finish 'em all before leave work time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about the other people who helped as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well they were the same. They used to work in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you ever feel that you were a favourite because you were the son?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. None whatever. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You didn't have to serve any apprenticeship because you were doing your apprenticeship without the name of it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you ever a member of any professional organization? Was there any sort of league of blacksmiths or league of foundry-men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no. No. No. You see, now - now that's one thing that - that I don't agr
ee with. Most all - tradesmen today - they're taught technically. Well - it isn't like practical experience. You see? Now you take my chap now that's carry on, I've brought him up my way, practically, you see? Theory's all right up to a point. Now there's
 
a chap - no scholar, he's a very poor scholar, but as far as practical work - he's first class. You see? Theory's all right to those that it appl - applies. But - some youngsters, you'd never drive it into 'em. And yet practically - they'll do a good job.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, definitely, all had the same interests.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You don't think there was a division of interest amongst workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. None whatever. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you think that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Well no I don't think so because - it's your future. You see, and I mean anybody with any incentive - knew you - you - sort of work - prepare for the future. It's always been my ambition, and - I've fulfilled it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you've had your own firm since 1939?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Yes, I feel now that - that - if it weren't for me health I should - I should still go on. But - when your health begins to break up well you've just go to take it a little easier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You're still actively interested though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh even now I'm actively interest - I must be doing something. Don't matter whether it's just buying and selling anything, or actually doing the work, but I must be doing something. Now wh
en it comes to - lifting or - or any heavy work, well I'll - those that I'm attached with, they - wouldn't hear of it and they just say now let it go, let it go, you see, well I've got to, I can't - I can't do it. But there's hundred and one things I can 
do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You continued living at home after you left school 'til you were about twenty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. When I come to Buckfastleigh.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you think starting full time work changed your relationship with your parents in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh none whatever. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How about your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 They didn't sort of treat you more like an adult once you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you spend Sunday any differently once you left school? Did you go to Sunday school still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well, yes, and as I say - after me Sunday school days I took up church you see, and - me - organ blowing to do and I had me bell-ringing to do that - it was - more or less the same thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you take any interest in politics during those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 None. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You didn't take part in any election activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. None.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you used to go round to the Liskeard billiard rooms, Liberal club and the Conservative club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. - Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When was that, was that after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 After I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you ever have anything like a bike in those days after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
A bike? Oh yes, good lord. I always remember the first bike I bought second hand and I think it in they days it was somewhere about fifte
en shilling. And then that's one thing - father did - give me and I had a - I had a - sort of fight hard for it and he give me a brand new one. Then when I got - a teenager, a brand new one, I was some proud of that bike. That was really marvellous, like 
a motor car to me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 The motor cars were just coming in then I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your friends have bikes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Beg pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your friends have bikes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, we all did when it got to that stage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So you were able to go bike rides?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
We - well and we used to go off - playing football and always cycle, all of us. Cycle - so far as - well the furthest then would be perhaps seven or eight miles. But most of the adjoining villages, about a mile, couple of mile apart. We alway
s push biked. Had to - get there ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So you kept up with your garden and pigs and things still after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you used to go to Duloe church to help with the ringing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no, we were all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you meet any new people after leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, yes, you'd get - changes of course, you'd get people coming - even villages and you naturally - especially in, as I 
say - country places you - they jolly soon muck in together. It isn't like a town where - well your next neighbour hardly know ee. But - in the country place everybody knows everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you ever bring friends home very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Where would you go with friends, just bike riding around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That's right, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Visiting other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your parents meet your friends very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well yes, they used to meet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no. That's - only - only thing that - personally if I should be late home father wanted to know where I'd been, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What time were you expected to be home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh he expected us in early in those days, when us was - youngsters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well not later than say ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How long had you known your wife when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh I - when I started to do me post round. When I was - well I should say - 'cos I done - I d
one - most of the rounds connected with St Kean post office, there was one - two - three, three separate rounds, and - in turn I did 'em all. Now for instance if my uncle that was a full time postman, Trewrdlen round, if he was on holiday or sick or anyth
i
ng - me knowing the district Mrs Pengelly would say well Les, would you do while Uncle John's ill, would you do Trewrdlen round? And he'd give perhaps - my sister for one to do mine little round, and that's how we used to carry on. Well when I started to 
do the Duloe round, 'cos St Kean approaches the Duloe parish, and - my present wife - I should say when I knew her first she was round about fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 And how old would you be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 About twelve months younger than her. So I was about thirteen when I 
went to that round, when I knew her first, and we - we often talk about it now, only told about it last night. Because we have our joke naturally, and - I used to go to their cottage with the post, then I used to - walk through a - a footpath through the 
f
ield to a farm, and then instead of coming back that way I used to go across the fields to the next farm. Well from her cottage she could see me going for them and always used to wave to me, when she was young, that's when I knew her first. Well - of cour
s
e we weren't serious until - I was probably - well about sixteen, when I started to go to church. And we courted for - for - oh must have been three years. And then we - well like all other youngsters I suppose, had our little tiffs, and - I always rememb
er what happened one Sunday night we went to church, and - she never spoke to me, all the time we was in church or after church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you sitting next to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 On the way home - so when I used to go there I used to leave me bike inside the
ir little garden gate and walk up a path to the house, I always used to leave me bike just inside the gate, this particular Sunday night - I'd come - come home with her from church, and - when we got to the gate - I opened the gate and took me bike, then 
s
he said - what we going to do now on? I said, I'm going home and next time I come perhaps you'll be better tempered. That's the word I used. And I went home. And the following - weekend, 'cos in those days we never used to meet in the week - good lor' we 
couldn't afford - that, and - the following Sunday - I thought to myself well shall I go to Duloe this evening, or go to - Looe. And \endash 
 I tossed up a coin, and - heads for Duloe, tails for Looe. He come down tails and I didn't hesitate, I went off to Looe. We often tell about it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What was at Looe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Down in Looe, well to - Looe wasn't - Looe was about - three and a half miles from our place, go down there on pushbike in about - quarter of an hour easy, and - this particular - Sunday I went to Loo
e, and there was a - a girl - in service on a big estate in Duloe parish, she used to attend Duloe church, regularly every Sunday morning, and I always remember her name, Mabel Cox, always remember Mabel, and - I went into Looe, walking along the quay, an
d
 I run up against Mabel, and of course this - natural she knew me through going to church and we had a chat you see. So - I always remember it, I went in the - went in the cafe and had my tea, and - arranged to take her home, in the evening. And - now you
 
talk about gentry. This is what happened in this partic - par - particular case, we walked up the Looe Valley about a mile - mile and a half, then we had to cross over the railway line, a level crossing, and then up the drive to the big house where she wo
r
ked. Well up where this big hours was was more than half way home for me. You see? And - we crossed the railway line, got over to the - drive entrance gate, and Mabel said - well I'm afraid you can't go any further than this. So I said, well what do you m
e
an? Her said, oh nobody's allowed up the drive. So I said, oh why? Oh they - they - our gentry won't allow anybody up the drive. I said, look if I'm good enough to come this far, I'm good enough to take you home. So I said, come on. I'm going - take you r
i
ght home. Her said, oh no, I - I can't - I said, now look - you leave it - I'll take it, if there's any trouble, you tell Squire Peel to come to me. Because - Squire Peel - owned all the property there, he was a squire, and he had a little - blacksmith's 
s
hop that my father rented. And father used to go there about two days a week, to - they used to have horses, hunters and so on, and he used to do all their shoeing. Well Mrs Peel, she was a very nice lady, and - and I was only a youngster then, and she kn
ew me through coming to the blacksmith's shop with these horses you see, so however this particular Sunday night I took Mabel up - took her up home, and outside the big house there was a lot of \endash 
 rorydendra - shrubs than anything, and footpaths in each way 
you see, so actually you couldn't see the house. So - and of course she was - she was on eggs afraid that somebody was going to see me. But - I took her up to the - to the path entrance and I said goodnight and off I went. Well I was nearly home. Well the
n
 - I courted her for a while. And of course my wife - she apparently was upset but in - in the meantime she picked up with another chap, in fact got engaged to him, but - she threw it off in the end, she - she never did really - want him, but there it was
.
 And - when I come to Buckfastleigh and that's how we got together again, I used to go home - and visit me friends same as I always did, and I was down at farmer Bill Slade's one Saturday evening and this his youngest brother used to work there. You see, 
h
e was working on this farm, and I was sat in the - in the farmhouse kitchen window, Mrs Slade was sitting opposite me, they had big long table, you know what a farmhouse is, they always sit, Bill was sitting up head of the table, we was having tea. And Mr
s
 Slade, she started to laugh, roared with laughing. And he - her husband said - oh what's got hold of you missus? So her said, I was just thinking about Les. Her said - her said, Bess is down St Dennis staying with her brother. Her said - I expect you kno
w
 her and - Bill Harris have parted and hers gone down there out of the way. You see, well I was taking all this in. And her said - I said to Cecil, her brother, her said, I said to Cecil times her said, you see if I ant right, Les and Bess'll get together
 
again yet. Her said, they was made for each other. Her said, you see if I aint right. And - Bill, her husband - said, well I shouldn't be surprised at that. Well I come home - to Buckfastleigh that weekend, and I wrote to her. And I said, I understand you
'
re staying down St Dennis. I said, I shall be coming home the weekend, and - if you wish to see me - I'll - come out. So she wrote back and said that - yes, she would come home the weekend and - if I would meet her at Liskeard - a motor bike, that I would
 
meet her at Liskeard station - somewhere about three o'clock in the afternoon, she'd be there. When I got down that Saturday afternoon Liskeard station, a pal of mine that I went to school with used to drive his own little taxi, from - Liskeard station up
 
to the town, he was - he was called Hicks, and - when he saw me get me off me motor bike and come - by the wall, he said - you looking for Miss Broad? So I said, yes, we - agreed to meet here, she's coming up from St Austell station. Well he said - I saw 
h
er just now, and a farmer out that way - offered to give her a lift home and her said if you come you was to go out to her house you see. So I said, oh that's all right, well then of course I jumped on me bike and went out to Duloe to her home, and - left
 me bike outside the path where I used to put me pushbike, walks up and rang the doorbell, and her mother come out. Poor old mother, I shall never forget it. And she said, my word, 'tis Les. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 She wasn't expecting you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. So - she said - 
well of course then - me wife, Bessie she was called, she come out the - the doorway and she said, oh come in. And of course that - that was that. Well then - we - got back together again and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What was the distance between St Kean and Duloe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh about a - no, only about - well it isn't much more than a mile and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Where was St Dennis, was that very for away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh, that's down near St Austell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Is that quite a way away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. I should say - well fifteen mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Between the time when you were up in Buckfastleigh did you write letters back to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You'd go and see her every weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Every weekend I used to go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 The first time you met her parents, I suppose you'd meet them through the post round first of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, I knew 'em - from a youngster, the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What was the first time you actually went into her house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well I used to go in there cottage in the - very early days. Used to go in there with the post, specially wintertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 It wasn't an arranged meeting or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no. When I was ringing you see, I used to take her home and we used to spend our evening, especially winter evenings indoor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they know your people at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 I suppose in a small area like that everyone knows everybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Everybody knows everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So it wasn't a case that they were pumping you with questions about where your parents lived and things like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How did you get on with your parents in law after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh - absolutely - top hole, yes. In fact - the wife's mother came with us to live after father died, and lived with us for - somewhere about twelve years after that. She had eig
hty - mother was eighty-four when she passed away here at Buckfastleigh, and we took her to Cornwall, with her - with her hus - buried her with her husband in Duloe parish church. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Can you remember the first time, did you ever go drinking with your father in law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Never. No, they were dead nuts against drink in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you ever help her parents with any odd jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you swap gardening hints or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, because her father was a gardener, and the boys - their sons gardeners, see. No, I didn't have to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you do anything round the house for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well such a thing as bringing in coal in the coal scuttle, because in those days there was no gas or electricity. Only oil lamps 
you see, the table lamps all oil lamps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What would you call her parents before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What were they called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What did you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - dad and mother, same as me own parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you call them that after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When you had your daughter did you still call them mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. That didn't change at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You didn't call them granny and granddad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Can you remember the first time that your wife met your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, she - she - visited me in St Kean, when we were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Can you remember the first time she came over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well - just the same thing, we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did she often come over to visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Sometimes once a week if - we - a
s we used to go - Liskeard perhaps of a Saturday evening, then we'd pop in home. That's how we used to carry on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was she the first girl you'd ever brought home for your parents to meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well - yes, she would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your parents ever ward you off certain other girls or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well - naturally, you know what youngsters are, we used to - mix up with girls, especially in country villages. Have little - have little chats and jokes and games together and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your parents ever encourage you to go out with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no. No, they never - that's up to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say both sets of parents knew each other quite well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How did they first meet, the two sets of parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well - mother used
 to come to St Keans, I've known her come over there perhaps to a furniture sale and then pop in home and have a little chat. You see? And of course father was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they see much of each other after you were married, the two sets of parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, we used to - go home and - yes, and they used to come our place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you'd only see each other once a week at weekends to begin with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of things would you do together at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, just - go for a walk or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did she have a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Oh she had a push bike. We used to - go to Liskeard of a - Saturday evening and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would she play billiards as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. Oh no, she didn't take any - any - part in that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of things would you do in Liskeard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well - oh just look around the shops and - walk around, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were the shops open on Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, in those days. Yes, open until - about eight o'clock, Saturday night. That's when p
eople used to do their main shopping. They couldn't afford time in the week, they were working. Christmas time they'd be open 'til nearly midnight. Christmas Eve. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When you were courting did they come over to Christmas at all, did you have Christmas together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well I don't remember ever 'em coming on the Christmas time because as I said nearly everybody - are home on their own Christmastime.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Would you go over there at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Of course, that's natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you still go out with other friends at the same time, did you still go out playing billiards and things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes. The men. Always. And it's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How would you fit in both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well we - we - as I say, it was only at weekends we used to meet. 
Ordinary evenings I'd be playing billiards, you see? As I say we just - well I don't suggest it cost ee any money to go to visit people but the point is that - it was a - a system that you had in those days - it was quite enough to see each other about on
ce a week. Now youngsters, good lor', they've - got to meet every with each other. Well we had something else to do as the saying is in those days. Well, that - that was the tradition in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you go on any holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Never. Never. No. 
holiday. The only holiday I ever had in me life was when I got married and we had a week at me - wife's brother at St Dennis. We went down there for a week. That's only - holiday we both ever had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You said the moment you decided to get married was when you gave her the ultimatum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Yes. Oh yes. Yes. Yes, well you see - she was - I was twenty-seven, she was twenty-eight, so I mean - and - and - it was come to the stage that well - it was my future, and - if she hadn't settled down then - well - in a
ll probability I might have picked up with a girl here in Buckfastleigh and married within three or six months. I mean you got to - you got to look for the future in any case. Everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 It had been going on for fifteen years then hadn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did one of you actually say will you marry me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
No. No, didn't say actually will you marry me. But - I popped the question many times while I was here working in the four years, and - wife always used to say well - oh we can go o
n a little bit longer like we'm going and I just did, 'til the time come that when I was - me own boss offered me a house and permanent job, then there was a future. And then I decided it was time to make a definite decision. And I said, well now the time
'
s come, if you can't make up your mind to go, I'm afraid, we shall have to part, and that'll be the end of it. Well then she saw I was really serious, and she jolly soon - well the words she used was - all right I'll go and chance it. And naturally I said
, there's nothing for you to chance no more than me, it's both our own response - both our responsibility.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How long were you separated when you say you had this tiff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh not more than - twelve months. It wasn't very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So when you decided to get married it didn't come as too much of a surprise to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
No, you see, as I say the second time that we - we met up again, I went then and must have been - three - I was up here about twelve months, so it's three years that I was going to and 
fro. And I often used to say - about settling down, because - I actually tried - looked for a cottage, I thought to myself well if I can get a cottage here - she may alter her mind. Well - I couldn't get anything. And - when the boss offered me a cottage 
well then the time had come - that I had to have a definite decision, and that's how it come about. You see?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have to ask your parents permission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. Not whatever. Good lor' when you'm twenty-seven or eight 'tis time for you to make up y
our own minds. And I'd been independent of 'em for years you see. I had to paddle me own canoe for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have to ask her parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When did you tell your parents, the same night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh the same time, yes, same weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were they pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you ever engaged as such?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, we were engaged for - quite a while. Quite a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 All the time you were in Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well not - not - not very long after we met up again. Yes. I offered her the ring and she accepted it. And of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was it possible to be engaged in those days without having a ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Not really. It's a - that is a tradition. - We didn't have any - song about it, or any party or anything. You couldn'
t do it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of ring was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh very nice - ring. As far as I was concerned in those days 'til as good as anybody could give.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you ever have any other rings after you got married, like wedding rings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well she had her wedding ring of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Anything like an eternity ring?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have things like valentines or love spoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well lots do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was there an announcement in the paper at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well in our local papers. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When you got engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Not when we got engaged, only when we married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How did you choose your wedding ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - the wife. I took her to Plymouth and - I sad, now, you choose what you want. And she had what she wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 And you paid for it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you save up much before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Well I couldn't save very much, because - my wages were only two guineas a week. And I used to go home at weekends, it would cost me at least a pound a weekend to go home and - shilling or two we spent home and then back again you see so, I didn't -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You used to have a motor bike did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Motor bike. See I did have a little bit of money that I saved on the - what I had left from me pigs. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What happened to them when you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well then I had to finish with it. See all I had were me - was me wages at foundry. And I was down there twenty years. Well then - when I come I thought to myself well, to prepare for me old age I've got t
o do something different from this and I went in business on me own, now I don't regret it. Because I had the - instinct to - go ahead. And - I suppose - lot I got to be thankful for, I happened to have started at the right time. When the war was on. And 
of course - made money. Mind I had to pay the government quite a lot of it in income tax. But now we're - reasonably well situated.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your wife keep a bottom drawer or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh my word, yes. She's been - a wonderful wife. She man
aged - reared up our child - on two pound a week. Kept her mother for - twelve years on her bare ten shilling a week pension. And she saved money on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Before she got married did she have a bottom drawer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, she did. She's one of the - one of the - real - old fashioned - girls, she prepared. How she did it I do not know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say the Wilcox's offered you a cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you buy much household equipment before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - the wife - well between us we did. In fact as I told you our furniture - sixty pound I spent furniture and expensed and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did your parents help in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 They couldn't. They hadn't got anything to help us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Who did you first see to arrange about the wedding? Did you go along to the vicar first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well - our - Duloe - vicar you see, I was a ringer and - we used to attend church, and father a gardener there, that was quite simple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How long before the wedding was it that you went to see him about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh, 
matter of - a week or two. 'Cos we did have a little time to play with. He - he offered me this cottage in - April and we got married in July, beginning of July. So I had plenty of time to - prepare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was there any particular reason for the wedding date you chose, why July?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well, I wasn't bound because - we went in - to St Dennis for a week, honeymoon you see, so - we weren't bound to time as far as the cottage was concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was there any real reason for choosing July?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, just as we - what we could arrange.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Why did you choose a religious ceremony?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
Oh well that's - typical of these country villages, you - you - you - in those days - it would be a crime to get married in a Registry Office. That's natural, we were church go
ing people and - and of course it's - everybody else is happy with a church wedding or even a chapel wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have any difficulty getting your parents agreement at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you want a large or a small wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh, just ordinary family affair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How did you decide who to invite, you often get these stories of so many relatives and neighbours don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well we - there wasn't anybody invited outside, a lot of 'em come for the wedding because they knew us s
o well. They didn't want - they don't - they don't - in those days we didn't - they didn't expect an invitation. They come and they come and we was pleased to see 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you send any invites out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 None - none whatever no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How did you arrange the reception and thins like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well we just had it at the wife's home, after the wedding we come back to the wife's home. And just the two families you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 It's really the families rather than friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How many of the families would be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh - all of the two families, all the relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 All of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Her brothers and sisters and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Aunts and uncles?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How many did that involve altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Wel
l our family see we were five, I - I think - I don't think me eldest sister attended that wedding. And of course me - she - she - and the youngest daughter was away - her youngest sister was away, but father and mother and - brothers, and same - the wife'
s side, her brothers. In fact her brother, eldest brother at St Dennis gave - gave her away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Who was your best man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh now you've asked me something. Who the Dickens was it? Somebody in the village. I can't think who it was for a minute. Somebody
 in the village. Probably the wife will remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That was about the limit of the guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You didn't have your aunt from Liskeard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they go to the wedding, the actual church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh from home they did of course yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So it was all done by word of mouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 But you did have an advert put in the paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 In the - local Cornish Times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 So there wouldn't be any question of anyone having to stay overnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How were the costs of the wedding met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Beg pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 How were the costs of the wedding met, who paid for all that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well I - I did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Not the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, they hadn't - they couldn't help - us, we couldn't expect them to. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you do anything special the last week before the wedding, have a stag party or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, nothing whatever. I just left me job and went home and - we had the wedding and - off we went to St Dennis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did anything happen on the last day at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Nothing whatever. Nothing whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Nor presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No well they - they couldn't afford it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about first day back after the wedding? Anything happen then when you got back to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When I got back to work? Oh nothing. Nothing whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you see your wife on the wedding day before the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, that's a tradition, you - you don't - in those days, I don't say now, but - in those days, it was - well - I'm 
going so far as to say it was nearly a crime to see your partner before you met at the church. It was in those days. You daren't see each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have things like ushers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes. Yes. Members of our own family of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What about groomsmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, just the normal -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What did you both wear for the wedding?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh just ordinary - ordinary clothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You didn't sort of have Moss Bros special or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh good lor' no, we couldn't afford that in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you wear something old, something new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. Just ordinary suit of clothes and - wife had on her wedding dress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did the bride have attendants? How did you decide on the dress for the bride and her attendants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh I just - left that to the wife, I had nothing whatever to do with that. Don't interest me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did she go and pick her own dress and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, oh yes, she did everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What kind of dress did she wear on the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh my word, I'm afraid you've asked me a question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did she ever wear it again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
I don't think so, not really. I expect - I expect if the truth's known she's got it now. As far as I know. My word, if you saw all her - wardrobes. Well I wouldn't know what's in the house. Oh fantastic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have anything like flower girls or page boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did year flowers, did your wife wear flowers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh just buttonholes you know. All had our buttonholes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What did you do with them afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well the - we kept 'em - as long as we could and - it was natural flowers, they - they just perished in the end but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Why are the bride's and grooms guests separated in church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 The bride and groom's? The - the bride?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Your wife's side of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well, yes, what they normally do is - one family sit one side of pews and the other the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you know why that is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Well it's a tradition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say that you went back to her place afterwards for a reception?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes, for a reception.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What was that like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh just a normal meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh, normal - normal meal, well sandwiches and - just a normal meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was it a sit down affair or buffet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh sit down affair to the table. Of course we couldn't all sit the once, we'd have a couple of goes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you on the first or second sitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you at the head of the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh no, I don't think so, we just - sat anywhere we wished. Just a family affair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have to get to the house first before everybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, we all are - arrived back together from church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have a car or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, we had cars. Hired cars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were you first in the cars going out from the church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Yes? You see I was the first to church, and then - the - groom always - goes in the church first and wait 'til the bride comes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you get any presents on leaving the church, did your wife get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Not on leaving the church, we had - not - not - well yes, we had horseshoes of course we did have - that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 When were they given to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh when - wife got in the car to go off to the station for honeymoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you go straight, how long was it before you left the reception and went off on honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh matter of about a couple of hours. We had to go Liskeard station you see to catch the train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did anyone play any tricks on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. Bar confetti of course, we were smothered in that stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did anyone throw any rose petals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, and - of course we had the - the bells were rung, 'cos I was a ringer you see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they decorate the carriages at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, just ordinary ribbon on the car.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there any photographs taken?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, we had our photographs taken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Who did that, one of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No, we had - outside photographer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was the wedding covered by the press, the local paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, in the local Cornish Times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 With photographs and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Beg pardon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did they have photographs in the press?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Just the bride and - bridegroom that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say that only family came back to the reception?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 But there'd be a lot more in church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh quite a number. Yes. 'Cos the wife was well - well known in Duloe you see and all her friends and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you have a cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh well naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Who baked that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 I - I believe the wife - made it herself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did it have icing and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did it have any sort of inscriptions on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Now that I - I'm afraid I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 What happened to the cake afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 My word, I'm afraid he was soon demolished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you pack it up and send it to other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, to our - relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were there any wedding presents on display at the reception?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did anyone make speechless?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Was there any dancing or singing or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You say you went on your honeymoon to St Dennis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 St Dennis to our honeymoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 And you left after about a couple of hours at the reception?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 You stayed there for a week did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 A week we had at St Dennis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 And then you moved up into your cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Mov
ed back to our cottage. And the following - we come back a Saturday - afternoon and - did a bit of shopping in the town, and then of course Monday morning I started - foundry again to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you go straight back up to Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 That was the first time your wife saw that cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Yes. Oh no, she saw it before we - 'cos we had plenty of time you see. She saw it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 She went up there for a weekend before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, she come up a time or two before. We moved in then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Did you carry your wife over the threshold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Do you remember attending any other weddings when you were a youngster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Oh yes, to me own - personal friends of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5273668 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Were they about the same as your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138623 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 Exactly the same.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \fi-490\li518\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid5273668 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14307531\charrsid11994791 
\par }}